\cf0 If both ladders give the same H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f1 , neither set of systematics can plausibly be hiding a systematic that fakes a tension with Planck. If they disagree, the disagreement itself is informative about which set of systematics is misbehaving.\
This is why the H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f1  tension debate has been substantially structured around the 
\f0\b Pop-I (Cepheid) ladder vs Pop-II (TRGB) ladder
\f1\b0  comparison. SH0ES is the canonical Pop-I result; CCHP is the canonical Pop-II result. Their disagreement is the methodological centerpiece of the field.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 The Pop-II ladder, end-to-end\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Let me trace the pathway through a representative Pop-II measurement so the structure is concrete:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Anchor
\f1\b0 : NGC 4258 maser distance (7.58 Mpc, 1.5%) 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b Calibrator step 1
\f1\b0 : Identify TRGB stars in NGC 4258 halo, measure tip apparent magnitude $m_\{\\rm TRGB,N4258\}$ 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b TRGB tip absolute magnitude
\f1\b0 : $M_\{\\rm TRGB\} = m_\{\\rm TRGB,N4258\} - \\mu_\{\\rm N4258\}$ 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b Calibrator step 2
\f1\b0 : Identify TRGB stars in halos of nearby SN Ia host galaxies, measure tip apparent magnitudes 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b SN Ia host distances
\f1\b0 : $\\mu_i = m_\{\\rm TRGB,i\} - M_\{\\rm TRGB\}$ 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b SN Ia absolute magnitude
\f1\b0 : from light curves of SN Ia in the calibrator hosts, knowing their distances, derive $M_B^0$ 
\f6 \uc0\u8595 
\f1  
\f0\b Hubble flow
\f1\b0 : apply $M_B^0$ to Hubble-flow SN Ia at 0.02 < z < 0.1, fit $H_0$ from the Hubble diagram zero point.\
The structure is identical to SH0ES \'97 same anchor, same SN Ia rung \'97 but with TRGB substituted for Cepheids in the middle. The cleanness of the substitution is what makes Pop-I vs Pop-II such a powerful comparison: any systematic that differs between the two must live specifically at the calibrator rung.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

